included.description:
Worked on NN/g's 3rd web-wide usability study since 1990s, researching on the top UX issues that still existing today. Designed, ran and analyzed studies for more than 120 participants in US and UK on wide range of websites.

Independently ran 2 local studies in China. A study on WeChat (the most popular message/service platform app in China) via diary study and usability testing. Published an article with Jakob Nielsen at https://www.nngroup.com/articles/wechat-integrated-ux/. Another bonus research article on QR code and shake gesture at: https://www.nngroup.com/articles/wechat-qr-shake/

Independently run another local study to compare how Chinese and foreign users deal with websites in different complexities from busy portal sites to Bootstrap-style modern sites.
included.title: UX Research Assistant

included.description: Conducted user experience and visual design for Derm for Primary Care's new site, aiming to bring high quality, accessible, easy-to-use online learning experience to dermatologists. Led end-to-end new feature (Diagnosis Algorithm) design process and migrated the whole site payment mechanism to subscription service. Also led on graphic design, illustrations, and branding.
included.title: Product Design Intern

included.description:
Yinglink is a young startup based in Beijing, serving radiologists to share and discuss their film cases in order to improve their own skills and help patients. 

I was working as the first product designer, responsible for the whole process of mobile app design and deliverables, working with marketing, development and medical consultant team. Yinglink is now available in Chinese app store for both iOS and Android, with more than 5w users.
included.title: Product Design | Yinglink

included.description:

Tools/methods we use: interviews, contextual inquiry, stakeholder map, customer journey map, service blueprint, storyboarding, interface mockup, and great teamwork.
